        "FIGREF0": {
            "text": "Fig.\u00a01: Possible hypothesis of pulmonary embolism in COVID-19. Cytokine surge secondary to viremia causes endothelial dysfunction. Presence of anti-\u03b22 glycoprotein/antiphospholipid antibodies in COVID-19 could be a potential cause of pulmonary thrombosis. IL-1: Interleukin-1, IL-1\u03b2: Interleukin-1\u03b2, IL-6: Interleukin-6, Interferon-\u03b3: Interferon-\u03b3, and TNF-\u03b1:Tumor necrosis factor-\u03b1.",
